text: Brož at the 2017 luge world cup in Oberhof. Antonín Brož (, born December 14, 1987 in Jablonec nad Nisou) is a Czech luger who has competed since 2002. He finished 16th in the men's doubles event at the 2006 Winter Olympics in Turin. Brož finish 19th in the men's doubles event at the 2007 FIL World Luge Championships in Igls. He competes in doubles with his brother Lukáš. ==References== * 2006 luge men's doubles results * FIL-Luge profile == External links == * * * Category:1987 births Category:Living people Category:People from Jablonec nad Nisou Category:Czech male lugers Category:Lugers at the 2006 Winter Olympics Category:Lugers at the 2014 Winter Olympics Category:Lugers at the 2018 Winter Olympics Category:Olympic lugers of the Czech Republic
